geneVariantDescriptions.description: NOTCH3 over exp indicates an over expression of the Notch3 protein. However, the mechanism causing the over expression is unspecified.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, treatment with Tarextumab (OMP-59R5) in combination with Gemzar (gemcitabine) resulted in tumor regression in patient-derived xenograft models of pancreatic cancer with high NOTCH3 expression (PMID: 25934888).

references.title: Targeting Notch signaling with a Notch2/Notch3 antagonist (tarextumab) inhibits tumor growth and decreases tumor-initiating cell frequency.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Nutlin-3 moderately inhibited growth of primary liver cancer cells over expressing target genes of the Notch (HES1, HEY1, TRIB2, NOTCH3, CCND1) and Hedgehog (GLI1, GLI2) pathways in culture (PMID: 27103434).
